Key Match Events: Dagur Thorsteinsson scored the only goal of the match in the 12th minute.
Ingi Ingason received a yellow card in the 45+1 minute.
Arnar Haraldsson received a yellow card in the 79th minute.
Finnsson received a yellow card in the 81st minute.
Pre-Game Insights: England's Euro 2024 hopefuls have one final chance to impress Gareth Southgate in this friendly encounter.
England made hard work of their clash with Bosnia-Herzegovina but still ran out 3-0 winners.
Iceland has not been in action since their Euros dreams were dashed by Ukraine in March.
Some players' efforts on June 7 may be futile against Iceland as Gareth Southgate announced his final 26-man selection on Thursday, axing seven players from his selection.
